_sText:
From wilderness to early morning town.



A map that I had been working on and off for the past 2 years.

For an average first time player it should take around 20-30 minutes with auto (30-40 mins scroll) to beat the map. Once you've beaten the map once, it should take around 10 minutes.
The map has a longjump room, a bonus and a secret.

Start and end zones are marked. HDR+Bloom recommended.

Bad framerate?

Enable multicore rendering (mat_queue_mode -1). This will improve rendering times, specifically static prop rendering. I did what I could to optimize the map and had to halt adding more detail because of this reason.

EDITS

25 Dec 2016 - Update 1 (u1) (Slight changes to make it easier)

A chill and pretty easy autobunnyhop map. Quite short (2-5 minutes). Can be beaten legit/400vel but whether it's enjoyable is another thing.
_Can you find all the hidden marks?_ ;)

- **Anti-aliasing might cause weird white lines. You have been warned.**
- Fps drops? Don't like how the map looks? **r_3dsky 0** is your friend!
- The underground part is not there to annoy you with 64-unit jumps. In fact, you can beat it without ever doing them. Perhaps your route needs to be changed... Who knows, maybe it's faster to do them on different modes...
- **Server owners**: Starting and ending zones are marked.

_sText:
Made this map in a day, hoped that would be it. Ended up with a heap of errors and bugs that needed fixing. Took longer than expected. Models are from [Blade Symphony](http://store.steampowered.com/app/225600/ "http://store.steampowered.com/app/225600/"). Buy it. Packing the map was a nightmare, the programs couldn't detect the model textures, and I couldn't figure them out manually because they don't have the same names as the models. It wasn't worth spending time packing the map correctly given how little time I spent making the map, so this is my half assed, pack everything and hope, unreasonably large file size, rage quit, effort of a map.

Visit [steamcommunity.com/groups/_strafe](https://steamcommunity.com/groups/_strafe "https://steamcommunity.com/groups/_strafe") for real bhop.


FIXED VERSION. Big ups to George for fixing the cheat and reducing the file size since I was too lazy to. Didn't change the name to _fix or _v2 since yuka asked nicely for it to be kept the same. _sText:
So, first map (2nd actually, first 'good' one hasn't been released yet). I created a bhop practice map, as you can see in the name, where there are different kind of courses to go through. Dont say that the design sucks, i know, i created this for 1-2 hours only. 

Spawns are in the same area, so choose whatever team you want.

Features:

-First, the large red squares. I know that you cant fall through them because they are too close to each other, but all you have to do is act that you can fall through. Im gonna have to put this in the next version.

-Light red sqaures. Like the other one, but you can actually fall through them! More spacing and smaller.

-Circles. A straight line of circles that you can fall through in between (kindof)

- The straight, slightly broken and the broken straight lines. They are just for ADAD air strafing bhops.

-There are two sides in the map, the short one, and the long one. The long one is just doubled the length of the short one.

- There is a ramp going downwards at the side of the map for downhill bhops.

- At the end of each course, the floor, and the bottom of the ramp, there are blue platforms (nothing on floor) that teleports you back in spawn.

Im free to suggestions because this is just the first version of the map. Im a new mapper so, this is just a first for me.

As i told up here in this post, i have an unreleased map and im planning to release it too. I dont think that i need to playtest it even more since both sides are symmetrical and its small and is a gungame map.

HOPE YOU LIKE IT!

UPDATE! - 5/27/12
==================
- Song now compiled inside map.
- Custom textures now compiled inside map.
- Name reduced for easier identification, now more "_build3"

Boxes Snowy
==================

This is my first ever released Bhop map. (on here that is.) It's been a really fun experience to add to my collection and I don't regret a bit of it.

About the map...
------------------
The map itself isn't too long, and I'd say ranged for the moderately experienced Bhopper. I tried to make it look as appealing as possible, and really set a nice mood for every snow fan to enjoy. I didn't use any regular snow textures just because I thought it looked silly, so I decided to use the bland dev texture, and add special interest to the snow around all the checkpoints with lights and other goodies. Oh, and there's also a song on a moderate volume to accompany you.
